result.execSummary:
The defendant Justin T Dvorak was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: If probation or extended supervision is allowed to expire or is revoked with outstanding financial obligations, the supervising agent shall notify the court 10 days prior to the revocation or discharge and provide current financial information.  A civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for any balances due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect all debt.
Must have no contact with C.J.W. d/o/b 11-13-1994.

Must complete any and all evaluations, counseling, treatment and follow-up recommended by Probation Agent.
Must undergo a sex offender evaluation. 
Court holds issue of sex offender registration open.
Expunction will be considered by the court after receipt of sex offender evaluation.

timeConds.notes: Entitled to 65 days jail credit if revoked.
